verb.description: Cover the surface of (something) with a coating.
examples: their fingernails were overlaid with silver or gold

verb.description: (of a quality or feeling) become more prominent than (a previous quality or feeling)
examples: his openness had been overlaid by his new self-confidence

noun.description: Something laid as a covering over something else.
The process of transferring a block of program code or other data into internal memory, replacing what is already stored.
